  string
  line 3
  line `THE ANDHRA PRADESH REORGANISATION ACT, 2014`
  line ___________
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line ___________
  line `PART I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `PART II`
  line `R EORGANISATION OF THE STATE OF ANDHRA PRADESH`
  line `3. Formation of Telangana State.`
  line `4. State of Andhra Pradesh and territorial divisions thereof.`
  line `5. Hyderabad to be common capital for States of Telangana and Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `6. Expert Committee for setting up of a capital for Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `7. Governor of existing State of Andhra Pradesh to be common Governor.`
  line `8. Responsibility of Governor to protect residents of common capital of Hyderabad.`
  line `9. Assistance of police forces from Central Government to successor States, etc.`
  line `10. Amendment of First Schedule to Constitution.`
  line `11. Saving powers of State Governments.`
  line `PART III`
  line `R EPRESENTATION IN THE LEGISLATURES`
  line `12. Amendment of Fourth Schedule to Constitution.`
  line `13. Allocation of sitting members.`
  line `14. Representation in House of the People.`
  line `15. Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies.`
  line `16. Provision as to sitting members.`
  line `17. Provisions as to Legislative Assemblies.`
  line `18. Representation of Anglo - Indian community.`
  line `19. Allocation of sitting members.`
  line `20. Duration of Legislative Assemblies.`
  line `21. Speaker, Deputy Speaker and rules of procedure.`
  line `22. Legislative Council for successor States.`
  line `23. Provisions as to Legislative Councils.`
  line `24. Amendment of Delimitation of Council Constituencies Order.`
  line `25. Chairman, Deputy Chairman and rules of procedure.`
  line `26. Delimitation of constituencies.`
  line `27. Power of Election Commission to maintain Delimitation Orders up - to date.`
  line `28. Amendment of Scheduled Castes Order.`
  line `29. Amendment of Scheduled Tribes Order.`
  line `PART IV`
  line `H IGH COURT`
  line `30. High Court of Judicature at Hyderabad to be common High Court till establishment of High Court`
  line `of Andhra Pradesh.`
