  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `31. High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `32. Judges of Andhra Pradesh High Court.`
  line `33. Jurisdiction of Andhra Pradesh High Court.`
  line `34. Special provision relating to Bar Council and advocates.`
  line `35. Practice and procedure in Andhra Pradesh High Court.`
  line `36. Custody of seal of Andhra Pradesh High Court.`
  line `37. Form of writs and other processes.`
  line `38. Powers of Judges.`
  line `39. Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  line `40. Transfer of proceedings from Hyderabad High Court to Andhra Pradesh High Court.`
  line `41. Right to appear or to act in proceedings transferred to Andhra Pradesh High Court.`
  line `42. Interpretation.`
  line `43. Savings.`
  line `PART V`
  line `A UTHORISATION OF EXPENDITURE AND DISTRIBUTION OF REVENUES`
  line `44. Authorisation of expenditure of Telangana State.`
  line `45. Reports relating to accounts of Andhra Pradesh State.`
  line `46. Distribution of revenue.`
  line `PART VI`
  line `A PPORTIONMENT OF ASSETS AND LIABILITIES`
  line `47. Application of Part.`
  line `48. Land and goods.`
  line `49. Treasury and bank balances.`
  line `50. Arrears of taxes.`
  line `51. Right to recover loans and advances.`
  line `52. Investments and credits in certain funds.`
  line `53. Assets and liabilities of State undertakings.`
  line `54. Public Debt.`
  line `55. Floating Debt.`
  line `56. Refund of taxes collected in excess.`
  line `57. Deposits, etc.`
  line `58. Provident Fund.`
  line `59. Pensions.`
  line `60. Contracts.`
  line `61. Liability in respect of actionable wrong.`
  line `62. Liability as guarantor.`
  line `63. Items in suspense.`
  line `64. Residuary provision.`
  line `65. Apportionment of assets or liabilities by agreement.`
  line `66. Power of Central Government to order allocation or adjustment in certain cases.`
  line `67. Certain expenditure to be charged on Consolidated Fund.`
