obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `THE ANDHRA PRADESH REORGANISATION ACT, 2014`
  line `A CT N O. 6 OF 2014`
  line `[1 st March, 2014.]`
  line `An Act to provide for the reorganisation of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh and for matters`
  line `connected therewith.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Sixty - fifth Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `PART I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short t itle. — This Act may be called the And hra Pradesh Reorganisation Act, 2014.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “appointed day” means the day 1 which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint;`
  line `( b ) “article” means an article of the Constitution;`
  line `( c ) “assembly constituency”, “council constituency” and “parliamentary constituency” have the`
  line `same meanings as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line `( d ) “Election Commission” means the Election Commission appointed by the President under`
  line `article 324;`
  line `( e ) “existing State of Andhra Pradesh” means the State of Andhra Pradesh as existing`
  line `immediately before the appointed day;`
  line `( f ) “law” includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye - law, rule, scheme, notification`
  line `or other instrument having, immediately before the appointed day, the force of law in the whole or in`
  line `any part of the existing State ofAndhra Pradesh;`
  line `( g ) “notified order” means an order published in the Official Gazette;`
  line `( h ) “population ratio”, in relation to the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, means the ratio`
  line `of 58.32: 41.68 as per 2011 Census;`
  line `( i ) “sitting member”, in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of the existing`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh, means a person who immediately before the appointed day, is a member of`
  line `that House;`
  line `( j ) “successor State”, in relation to the existing State of Andhra Pradesh, means the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or the State of Telangana, as the case may be;`
  line `( k ) “transferred territory” means the territory which on the appointed day is transferred from the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Pradesh to the State of Telangana;`
  line `( l ) “treasury” includes a sub - treasury; and`
  line `( m ) any reference to a district, mandal, tehsil, taluk or other territorial division of the existing`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh shall be construed as a reference to the area comprised within that territorial`
  line `division on the appointed day.`
  line `1. 2nd June, 2014, v ide n otification No. S.O. 655 (E), dated 4th March, 2014, see Gazette of Indi a, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3( ii ).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `PART II`
  line `R EORGANISATION OF THE S TATE OF A NDHRA P RADESH`
  line `3. Formation of Telangana State. — On and from th e appointed day, there shall be formed a new`
  line `State to be known as the State of Telangana comprising the following territories of the existing State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh, namely: —`
  line `Adilabad, Karimnagar, Medak, Nizamabad, Warangal, Ranga r edd y, Nalgonda,`
  line `Mahbubnagar, 1 [ Khammam (but excluding the Mandals of Kukunoor, Velairpadu and Bhurgampadu but`
  line `not including its revenue villages of Pinapaka, Morampalli Banzar, Bhurgampad, Nagineniprolu,`
  line `Krishnasagar, Tekula, Sarapaka, Iravendi, Mothepattinagar, Uppusaka, Sompalli and Nakripeta under the`
  line `Palvancha Revenue Division, and the Mandal s of Chintoor, Kunavaram, Vararamachandrapuram and`
  line `Bhadrach alam but not including the revenue village of Bhadrachalam under the Bhadrachalam Revenue`
  line `Division ) ] and Hyderabad districts,`
  line `and there upon the said territories shall cease to form part of the existing State ofAndhra Pradesh.`
  line `4. State of Andhra Pradesh and territorial divisions thereof. –– On and from the appointed day, the`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh shall comprise the territories of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh other than`
  line `those specified in section 3.`
  line `5. Hyderabad to be common capital for States of Telangana and Andhra Pradesh. –– ( 1 ) On and`
  line `from the appointed day, Hyderabad in the existing State of Andhra Pradesh, shall be the common capital`
  line `of the State of Telangana and the State of Andhra Pradesh for such period not exceeding ten years.`
  line `( 2 ) After expiry of the period referred to in sub - section ( 1 ), Hyderabad shall be the capital of the State`
  line `of Telangana 2 [and Amaravati shall be the new capital] for the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `3 [ Explanation 1]. –– In this Part, the common capital includes the existing area notified as the Greater`
  line `Hyderabad Municipal Corporation under the Hyderabad Municipal Corporation Act, 1955 (Hyderabad`
  line `Act No. 2 of 1956).`
  line `4 [ Explanation 2. — For the purposes of sub - section (2), the expression “Amravati” includes the capital`
  line `city areas notified under the provisions of the Andhra Pradesh Capital Region Development Authority`
  line `Act, 2014.]`
  line `6. Expert Committee for setting up of a capital for Andhra Pradesh. — The Central Government`
  line `shall constitute an expert committee to study various alternatives regarding the new capital for the`
  line `successor State of Andhra Pradesh and make appropriate recommendations in a period not exceeding six`
  line `months from the date of enactment of the Andhra Pradesh Reorganisation Act, 2014.`
  line `7. Governor of existing State of Andhra Pradesh to be common Governor. — On and from the`
  line `appointed day, the Governor of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall be the Governor for both the`
  line `successor States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana for such period as may be determined by the President.`
  line `8. Responsibility of Governor to protect residents of common capital of Hyderabad. — ( 1 ) On and`
  line `from the appointed day, for the purposes of administration of the common capital area, the Governor shall`
  line `have special responsibility for the security of life, liberty and property of all those who reside in such area.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, the responsibility of the Governor shall extend to matters such as law and order,`
  line `internal security and security of vital installations, and management and allocation of Government`
  line `buildings in the common capital area.`
  line `( 3 ) In discharge of the functions, the Governor shall, after consulting the Council of Ministers of the`
  line `State of Telangana, exercise his individual judgment as to the action to betaken:`
  line `Provided that if any question arises whether any matter is or is not a matter as respects which the`
  line `Governor is under this sub - section required to act in the exercise of his individual judgment, the decision`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 2014, s.2, for certain words (w.e.f. 29 - 5 - 2014).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2026, s. 2, for “and there shall be a new capital” (w.e.f. 2 - 6 - 202 4 ).`
  line `3. Explanation numbered as Explanation 1 thereof by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 2 - 6 - 2024).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 2 - 6 - 202 4 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `of the Governor in his discretion shall be final, and the validity of anything done by the Governor shall`
  line `not be called in question on the ground that he ought or ought not to have acted in the exercise of his`
  line `individual judgment.`
  line `( 4 ) The Governor shall be assisted by two advisors to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line `9. Assistance of police forces from Central Government to successor States, etc. — ( 1 ) The Central`
  line `Government shall assist the successor States of Andhra Pradeshand Telangana to raise additional police`
  line forces.
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government shall, for a period of three years, on and from the appointed day,`
  line `maintain and administer the Greyhound Training Centre in Hyderabad which shallfunction as a common`
  line `training centre for the successor States and, at the expiry of the said period, the existing Greyhound`
  line `Training Centre in Hyderabad shall become the training centre of the State of Telangana.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government shall assist the successor State of Andhra Pradesh to set up a similar`
  line `state - of the - art training centre at such place as the State Government of Andhra Pradesh may by order`
  line notify.
  line `( 4 ) The Central Government shall provide financial assistance to the successor States in setting up`
  line `new operational hubs for Greyhounds at such locations as the successor States may by order notify.`
  line `( 5 ) The Greyhound and OCTOPUS forces of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall be distributed`
  line `between the successor States after seeking options from the personnel and, each of these forces, on or`
  line `after the appointed day shall function under the respective Director General of Police of the successor`
  line States.
  line `10. Amendment of First Schedule to Constitution. — On and from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, underthe heading “I. THE STATES’’, ––`
  line `( a ) in the paragraph relating to the territories of the State of Andhra Pradesh, after the words,`
  line `brackets and figures “Second Schedule to the Andhra Pradesh and Madras (Alteration of Boundaries)`
  line `Act, 1959 (56 of 1959) ”, the following shall be inserted, namely: —`
  line `“and the territories specified in section 3 of the Andhra Pradesh Reorganisation Act, 2014”;`
  line `( b ) after entry 28, the following entry shall be inserted, namely: —`
  line `“29. Telangana: The territories specified in section 3 of the Andhra Pradesh Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 2014.”.`
  line `11. Saving powers of State Governments. — Nothing in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall be`
  line `deemed to affect the power of the Government of Andhra Pradesh or the Government of Telangana to`
  line `alter, after the appointed day, the name, area or boundaries of any district or other territorial division in`
  line `the State.`
  line `PART III`
  line `R EPRESENTATION IN THE L EGISLATURES`
  line `The Council of States`
  line `12. Amendment of F ourth Schedule to Constitution. — On and from the appointed day, in the`
  line `Fourth Schedule to the Constitution, in the Table, —`
  line `( a ) in entry 1, for the figures “18”, the figures “11” shall be substituted;`
  line `( b ) entries 2 to 30 shall be renumbered as entries 3 to 31, respectively;`
  line `( c ) after entry 1, the following entry shall be inserted, namely: —`
  line `“2. Telangana.............................................. 7”.`
  line `13. Allocation of sitting members. — ( 1 ) On and from the appointed day, eighteen sitting members of`
  line `the Council of States representing the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall be deemed to have been`
  line `elected to fill the seats allotted to the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, as specifiedin the First`
  line `Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `( 2 ) The term of office of such sitting members shall remain unaltered.`
  line `The House of the People`
  line `14. Representation in House of the People. — On and from the appointed day, there shall be`
  line `allocated 25 seats to the successor State of Andhra Pradesh, and 17 seats to the successor State of`
  line `Telangana, in the House of the People, and the First Schedule to the Representation of the People Act,`
  line `1950 (43 of 1950) shall be deemed to be amended accordingly.`
  line `15. Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies. — ( 1 ) On and from the appointed`
  line `day, the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 2008, shall stand amended as`
  line `directed in the Second Schedule to thisAct.`
  line `( 2 ) The Election Commission may conduct the elections to the House of the People and the`
  line `Legislative Assemblies of the successor States of Andhra Pradesh and Telanganaas per the allocation of`
  line `seats specified in the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 2008 as`
  line `amended by this Act.`
  line `16. Provision as to sitting members. — ( 1 ) Every sitting member of the House of the People`
  line `representing a constituency which, on the appointed day by virtue of the provisions of section 14, stands`
  line `allotted, with or without alteration of boundaries, to the successor States of Andhra Pradesh or Telangana,`
  line `shall be deemed to have been elected to the House of the People by that constituency as so allotted.`
  line `( 2 ) The term of office of such sitting members shall remain unaltered.`
  line `The Legislative Assembly`
  line `17. Provisions as to Legislative Assemblies. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub - section ( 2 ), the`
  line `number of seats in the Legislative Assemblies of the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, on and`
  line `from the appointed day, shall be 175 and 119, respectively.`
  line `( 2 ) In the Second Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), under the`
  line `heading “I. STATES”: —`
  line `( a ) for entry 1, the following entry shall be substituted, namely: —`
  line `1 2 3 4 5 6 7`
  line `“1. Andhra Pradesh 294 39 15 175 29 7 ”;`
  line `( b ) entries 25 to 28 shall be renumbered as entries 26 to 29, respectively;`
  line `( c ) after entry 24, the following entry shall be inserted, namely: —`
  line `1 2 3 4 5 6 7`
  line `“25. Telangana — — — — 119 19 12 ”.`
  line `18. Representation of Anglo - Indian community. — Notwithstanding any thing in sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 17 the Governor of the State may nominate one member each to the Legislative Assemblies of the`
  line `successor States to give representation to the Anglo - Indian community in accordance with article 333 of`
  line `the Constitution.`
  line `19. Allocation of sitting members. — ( 1 ) Every si tting member of the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Pradesh elected to fill a seat in that Assembly from a constituency which on the`
  line `appointed day by virtue of the provisions of section 17 stands allotted, with or without alteration of`
  line `boundaries, to the State of Telangana shall, on and from that day, cease to be a member of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of Andhra Pradesh and shall be deemed to have been elected to fill a seat in the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of Telangana from that constituency as so allotted.`
  line `( 2 ) All other sitting members of the Legislative Assembly of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `shall continue to be members of the Legislative Assembly of that State and any such sitting member`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
