  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `representing a constituency, the extent or the name of which are altered by virtue of the provisions of`
  line `section 17, shall be deemed to have been elected to the Legislative Assembly of Andhra Pradesh by that`
  line `constituency as so altered.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Legislative`
  line `Assemblies of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana shall be deemed to be duly constituted on the appointed`
  line day.
  line `20. Duration of Legislative Assemblies. — The peri od of five years referred to in clause ( 1 ) of article`
  line `172 shall, in the case of the Legislative Assembly of the State of Andhra Pradesh and of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the State of Telangana, be deemed to have commenced on the date on which it actually`
  line `commenced in the case of the Legislative Assembly of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `21. Speaker, Deputy Speaker and rules of procedure. — ( 1 ) The person who immediately before the`
  line `appointed day is the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall`
  line `continue to be the Speaker of that Assembly on and from that day and the members of that Assembly shall`
  line `choose from amongst the members of the Assembly, a member to be the Deputy Speaker of that`
  line Assembly.
  line `( 2 ) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall become the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `successor State of Telangana and until the Speaker is chosen by that Assembly, the duties of the office of`
  line `the Speaker shall be performed by the Deputy Speaker so appointed.`
  line `( 3 ) The rules of procedure and conduct of business of the Legislative Assembly of Andhra Pradesh as`
  line `in force immediately before the appointed day shall, until rules are madeunder clause ( 1 ) of article 208, be`
  line `the rules of procedure and conduct of business of the Legislative Assembly of Telangana, subject to such`
  line `modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by the speaker thereof.`
  line `The Legislative Councils`
  line `22. Legislative Council for successor States. — ( 1 ) There shall be constituted a Legislative Council`
  line `for each of the successorStates consisting of not more than 1 [58 members in the Legislative Council of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh ] and 40 members in the Legislative Council of Telangana in accordance with the`
  line `provisions contained in article 169 of the Constitution.`
  line `( 2 ) The existing Legislative Council of the State of Andhra Pradesh shall, on and from the appointed`
  line `day, be deemed to have been constituted as two Legislative Councils of the successor States and the`
  line `existing members shall be allotted to the Councils as specified in the Fourth Schedule.`
  line `23. Provisions as to Legislative Councils. — ( 1 ) On and from the appointed day, there shall be 2 [58`
  line `seats in the Legislative Council of Andhra Pradesh ] and 40 seats in the Legislative Council of Telangana,`
  line respectively.
  line `( 2 ) In the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), ––`
  line `( i ) in the Third Schedule, ––`
  line `3 [ ( a ) for the existing entry 1, the following entry shall be substituted, namely: ––`
  line `1 2 3 4 5 6 7`
  line `“ 1. Andhra Pradesh 58 20 5 5 20 8 ”; ]`
  line `( b ) after entry 7, the following entry shall be inserted, namely: —`
  line `1 2 3 4 5 6 7`
  line `“7A. Telangana 40 14 3 3 14 6”;`
  line `( ii ) in the Fourth Schedule, after the heading “Tamil Nadu” and the entries relating thereunder,`
  line `the following heading and the entries shall be inserted, namely: —`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2015, s. 2, for “50 members in the Legislative Council of Andhra Pradesh” (w.e.f. 29 - 4 - 2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “50 seats in the Legislative Council of Andhra Pradesh” (w.e.f. 29 - 4 - 2015).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for entry 1 (w.e.f. 29 - 4 - 2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
