  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line “TELANGANA
  line `1. Municipal Corporations.`
  line `2. Municipalities.`
  line `3. Nagar Panchayats.`
  line `4. Cantonment Boards.`
  line `5. Zila Praja Parishads.`
  line `6. Mandal Praja Parishads.”.`
  line `24. Amendment of Delimitation of Council Constituencies Order. — ( 1 ) On and from the appointed`
  line `day, the Delimitation of Council Constituencies (Andhra Pradesh) Order,2006 shall stand amended as`
  line `directed in Part I of the Third Schedule.`
  line `( 2 ) On and from the appointed day, the Delimitation of Council Constituencies (Telangana) Order,`
  line `2014, as specified in Part II of the Third Schedule shall apply to the successor State of Telangana.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government may, in consultation with the successor States of Andhra Pradesh, or as`
  line `the case may be, Telangana, by notification in the Official Gazette amend the Third Schedule.`
  line `25. Chairman, Deputy Chairman and rules of procedure. — ( 1 ) The person who immediately`
  line `before the appointed day is the Chairman of the Legislative Council of the existing State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh shall continue to be the Chairmanof that Council on and from that day and the members of that`
  line `Council shall choose from amongst the members of the Council, a member to be the Deputy Chairman of`
  line `that Council.`
  line `( 2 ) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Deputy Chairman of the Legislative Council of the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall become the Deputy Chairman of the Legislative Council of the`
  line `successor State of Telangana and until the Chairman is chosen by that Council, the duties of the office of`
  line `Chairman shall be performed by the Deputy Chairman so appointed.`
  line `( 3 ) The rules of procedure and conduct of business of the Legislative Council of Andhra Pradesh as in`
  line `force immediately before the appointed day shall, until rules are made under clause ( 1 ) of article 208, be`
  line `the rules of procedure and conduct of business of the Legislative Council of Telangana, subject to such`
  line `modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by the Chairman thereof.`
  line `Delimitation of constituencies`
  line `26. Delimitation of constituencies. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions contained in article 170 of the`
  line `Constitution and without prejudice to section 15 of this Act, the number of seats in the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the successor States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana shall be increased from 175 and 119`
  line `to 225 and 153, respectively, and delimitation of the constituencies may be determined by the Election`
  line `Commission in the manner hereinafter provided —`
  line `( a ) the number of seats to be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes in the`
  line `Legislative Assemblies of the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, respectively, having regard to`
  line `the relevant provisions of the Constitution;`
  line `( b ) the assembly constituencies into which each State referred to in clause ( a ) shall be divided,`
  line `the extent of each of such constituencies and in which of them seats shall be reserved for the`
  line `Scheduled Castes or for the Scheduled Tribes; and`
  line `( c ) the adjustments in the boundaries and description of the extent of the parliamentary`
  line `constituencies in each State referred to in clause ( a ) that may benecessary or expedient.`
  line `( 2 ) In determining the matters referred to in clauses ( b ) and ( c ) of sub - section ( 1 ), the Election`
  line `Commission shall have regard to th e following provisions, namely: ––`
  line `( a ) all the constituencies shall be single - member constituencies;`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-13
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Page 13`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `( b ) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable, be geographically compact areas, and in`
  line `delimiting them, regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries of administrative units,`
  line `facilities of communication and conveniences to the public; and`
  line `( c ) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes`
  line `shall, as far as practicable, be located in areas where the proportion of their population to the total`
  line `population is the largest.`
  line `( 3 ) The Election Commission shall, for the purpose of assisting it in the performance of its functions`
  line `under sub - section ( 1 ), associate with it self as associate members, five persons as the Central Government`
  line `may by order specify, being persons who are the members of the Legislative Assembly of the State or of`
  line `the House of the People representing theState:`
  line `Provided that none of the associate members shall have a right to vote or to sign any decision of the`
  line `Election Commission.`
  line `( 4 ) If, owing to death or resignation, the office of an associate member falls vacant, it shall be filled as`
  line `far as practicable, in accordance with the provisions of sub - section ( 3 ).`
  line `( 5 ) The Election Commission shall ––`
  line `( a ) publish its proposals for the delimitation of constituencies together with the dissenting`
  line `proposals, if any, of any associate member who desires publication thereof in the Official Gazette and`
  line `in such other manner as the Commission may consider fit, together with a notice inviting objections`
  line `and suggestions in relation to the proposals and specifying a date on or after which the proposals will`
  line `be further considered by it;`
  line `( b ) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line `specified; and`
  line `( c ) after considering all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the`
  line `date so specified, determine by one or more orders the delimitation of constituencies and cause such`
  line `order or orders to be published in the Official Gazette,`
  line `and upon such publication, the order or orders shall have the full force of law and shall notbe called in`
  line `question in any court.`
  line `( 6 ) As soon as may be after such publication, every such order relating to assembly constituencies`
  line `shall be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the concerned State.`
  line `27. Power of Election Commission to maintain Delimitation Orders up - to date. –– ( 1 ) The Election`
  line `Commission may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette, —`
  line `( a ) correct any printing mistakes in any order made under section 26 or any error arising therein`
  line `from inadvertent slip or omission; and`
  line `( b ) where the boundaries or name of any territorial division mentioned in any such order or orders`
  line `is or are altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for bringing such`
  line `order up - to - date.`
  line `( 2 ) Every notification under this section relating to an assembly constituency shall be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is issued, before the concerned Legislative Assembly.`
  line `Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes`
  line `28. Amendment of Scheduled Castes Order. –– On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Castes) Order, 1950 (C.O. 19), shall stand amended as directed in the Fifth Schedule to this`
  line Act.
  line `29. Amendment of Scheduled Tribes Order. –– On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Tribes) Order, 1950 (C.O. 22), shall stand amended as directed in the Sixth Schedule to this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-14
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Page 14`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  sourcePage 14
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `PART IV`
  line `H IGH C OURT`
  line `30. High Court of Judicature at Hyderabad to be common High Court till establishment of High`
  line `Court of Andhra Pradesh. –– ( 1 ) On and from the appointed day, ––`
  line `( a ) the High Court of Judicature at Hyderabad shall be the common High Courtfor the State of`
  line `Telangana and the State of Andhra Pradesh till a separate High Court for the State of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `is constituted under article 214 of the Constitution read with section 31 of t his Act;`
  line `( b ) the Judges of the High Court at Hyderabad for the existing State of Andhra Pradesh holding`
  line `office immediately before the appointed day shall become on that day the Judges of the common High`
  line Court.
  line `( 2 ) The expenditure in respect of salaries and allowances of the Judges of the common High Court`
  line `shall be allocated amongst the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana on the basis of population ratio.`
  line `31. High Court of Andhra Pradesh. –– ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of section 30, there shall be a`
  line `separate High Court forthe State of Andhra Pradesh (hereinafter referred to asthe High Court of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh) and the High Court of Judicature at Hyderabad shall become the High Court for the State of`
  line `Telangana (hereinafter referred to as the High Court at Hyderabad).`
  line `( 2 ) The principal seat of the High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall be at such place as the President`
  line `may, by notified order, appoint.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 2 ), the Judges and division courts of the High`
  line `Court of Andhra Pradesh may sit at such other place or places in the State of Andhra Pradesh other than its`
  line `principal seat as the Chief Justice may, with the approval of the Governor of Andhra Pradesh, appoint.`
  line `32. Judges of Andhra Pradesh High Court. –– ( 1 ) Such of the Judges of the High Court at`
  line `Hyderabad holding office immediately before the date of establishment of the High Court of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh as may be determined by the President, shall, from that date cease to be Judges of the High Court`
  line `at Hyderabad and become, Judges of the High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `( 2 ) The persons who by virtue of sub - section ( 1 ) become Judges of the High Court of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `shall, except in the case where any such person is appointed to be the Chief Justice of that High Court, rank`
  line `in that Court according to the priority of their respective appointments as Judges of the High Court at`
  line Hyderabad.
  line `33. Jurisdiction of Andhra Pradesh High Court. –– The High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall have,`
  line `in respect of any part of the territories included in the State of Andhra Pradesh, all such jurisdiction,`
  line `powers and authorityas, under the law in force immediately before the datereferred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 30, are exercisable in respect of that part of the said territories by the High Court at Hyderabad.`
  line `34. Special provision relating to Bar Council and advocates. –– ( 1 ) On and from the date referred to`
  line `in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30, in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961), in section 3, in sub - section ( 1 ), in`
  line `clause ( a ), for the words “Rajasthan, Uttar Pradesh”, the words “Rajasthan,Telangana, Uttar Pradesh” shall`
  line `be substituted.`
  line `( 2 ) Any person who immediately before the date referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30 is an`
  line `advocate on the roll of the Bar Council of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh and practising as an`
  line `advocate in the High Court at Hyderabad, may givehis option in writing, within one year from that date to`
  line `the Bar Council of such existing State, to transfer his name on the roll of the Bar Council of Telangana and`
  line `notwithstanding any thing contained in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961) and the rules made`
  line `the reunder, on suchoption so given his name shall be deemed to have been transferred on the roll of the`
  line `Bar Council of Telangana with effect from the date of the option so given for the purposes of the said Act,`
  line `and the rules made thereunder.`
  line `( 3 ) The persons other than the advocates who are entitled immediately before thedate referred to in`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30, to practise in the High Court at Hyderabad or any subordinate court thereof`
  line `shall, on and after that date, be recognised as such persons entitled also to practise in the High Court of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or any subordinate court there of, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-15
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Page 15`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `( 4 ) The right of audience in the High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall be regulated in accordance with`
  line `the like principles as immediately before the date referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30, are in force`
  line `with respect to the right of audience in the High Court at Hyderabad.`
  line `35. Practice and procedure in Andhra Pradesh High Court. –– Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Part, the law in force immediately before the datereferred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30 with respect to`
  line `practice and procedure in the High Court at Hyderabad shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in`
  line `relation to the High Court of Andhra Pradesh, and accordingly, the High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall`
  line `have all such powers to make rules and orders with respect to practice and procedure as are immediately`
  line `before that date exercisable by the High Court at Hyderabad:`
  line `Provided that any rules or orders which are in force immediately before the datereferred to in`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30 with respect to practice and procedure in the High Court at Hyderabad shall,`
  line `until varied or revoked by rules or orders made by the High Court of Andhra Pradesh, apply with the`
  line `necessary modifications in relation to practice and procedure in the High Court of Andhra Pradesh as if`
  line `made by that Court.`
  line `36. Custody of seal of Andhra Pradesh High Court. –– The law in force immediately before the date`
  line `referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30 with respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court at`
  line `Hyderabad shall, with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the custody of the seal of the`
  line `High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `37. Form of writs and other processes. –– The law in force immediately before the date referred to in`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30 with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded`
  line `by the High Court at Hyderabad shall, with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the form of`
  line `writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `38. Powers of Judges. – – The law in force immediately bef ore the date referred to in sub - s ection ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 30 relating to the powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and division courts of the High Court`
  line `at Hyderabad and with respect to all matters ancillary to the exercise of those powers shall, with the`
  line `necessary modifications, apply in relation to the High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `39. Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court. –– The law in force immediately before the date`
  line `referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30 relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court at`
  line `Hyderabad and the Judges and division courts thereof shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in`
  line `relation to the High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `40. Transfer of proceedings from Hyderabad High Court to Andhra Pradesh High Court. –– ( 1 )`
  line `Except as hereinafter provided, the High Court at Hyderabad shall, as from the date referred to in`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30, have no jurisdiction in respect of the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `( 2 ) Such proceedings pending in the High Court at Hyderabad immediately before the date referred to`
  line `in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30 as are certified, whether before or after that day, by the Chief Justice of that`
  line `High Court, having regard to the place of accrual of the cause of action and other circumstances, to be`
  line `proceedings which ought to be heard and decided by the High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall, as soon as`
  line `may be after such certification, be transferred to the High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) of this section or in section 3 3, but`
  line `save as hereinafter provided, the High Court at Hyderabad shall have, and the High Court of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh shall not have, jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to the`
  line `Supreme Court, applications for review and other proceedings where any such proceedings seek any relief`
  line `in respect of any order passed by the High Court at Hyderabad before the date referred to in su b - section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 30:`
  line `Provided that if after any such proceedings have been entertained by the High Courtat Hyderabad, it`
  line `appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh, he shall order that they shall be so transferred, and such proceedings shall thereupon be`
  line `transferred accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
