  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  sourcePage 16
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `( 4 ) Any order made by the High Court at Hyderabad ––`
  line `( a ) before the date referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30, in any proceedings transferred to`
  line `the High Court of Andhra Pradesh by virtue of sub - section ( 2 ), or`
  line `( b ) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court at Hyderabad retains jurisdiction by`
  line `virtue of sub - section ( 3 ),`
  line `shall for all purposes have effect, not only as an order of the High Court at Hyderabad, but also as an`
  line `order made by the High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `41. Right to appear or to act in proceedings transferred to Andhra Pradesh High Court. –– Any`
  line `person who, immediately before the date referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30, is an advocate`
  line `entitled to practise or any other persons entitled to practise in the High Court at Hyderabad and was`
  line `authorised to appear in any proceedings transferred from that High Court to the High Court of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh under section 40, shall have the right to appear in the High Court of Andhra Pradesh in relation to`
  line `those pr oceedings.`
  line `42. Interpretation. –– For the purposes of section 40, ––`
  line `( a ) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a court until that court has disposed of all issues`
  line `between the parties, including any issues with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings`
  line `and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for`
  line `review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs; and`
  line `( b ) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division`
  line `court thereof, and references to an order made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including`
  line `references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court or Judge.`
  line `43. Savings. –– Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the High Court of Andhra Pradesh of`
  line `any provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to anyprovision that may be`
  line `made on or after the date referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 30 with respect to that High Court by`
  line `any Legislature or other authority having power to make such provision.`
  line `PART V`
  line `A UTHORISATION O F EXPENDITURE AND DISTRIBUTION OF REVENUES`
  line `44. Authorisation of expenditure of Telangana State. –– The Governor of existing State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh may, at any time before the appointed day, authorise such expenditure from the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the State of Telangana as he deems necessary for any period not more than six months beginning`
  line `with the appointed day pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of the State`
  line `of Telangana:`
  line `Provided that the Governor of Telangana may, after the appointed day, authorise such further`
  line `expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Telangana for any period`
  line `not extending beyond the said period of six months.`
  line `45. Reports relating to accounts of Andhra Pradesh State. –– ( 1 ) The reports of the Comptroller`
  line `and Auditor - General of India referred to in clause ( 2 ) of article 151 relating tothe accounts of the existing`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh inrespect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be submitted to the`
  line `Governor of each of the successor States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana who shall cause them to be`
  line `laid before the Legislature of that State.`
  line `( 2 ) The President may by order ––`
  line `( a ) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of Andhra Pradesh on any`
  line `service in respect of any period prior to the appointed dayduring the financialyear or in respect of any`
  line `earlier financial year in excess of theamount granted for that service and for that year as disclosed in`
  line `the reports referred toin sub - section ( 1 ) to have been duly authorised; and`
  line `( b ) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-17
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Page 17`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  sourcePage 17
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `46. Distribution of revenue. –– ( 1 ) The award made by the Thirteenth Finance Commission to the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall be apportioned between the successor States by the Central`
  line `Government on the basis of population ratio and other parameters:`
  line `Provided that on the appointed day, the President shall make a reference to the Fourteenth Finance`
  line `Commission to take into account the resources available to the successor States and make separate awards`
  line `for each of the successor States.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything in sub - section ( 1 ), the Central Government may, having regard to the`
  line `resources available to the successor State of Andhra Pradesh, make appropriate grants and also ensure that`
  line `adequate benefits and incentives in the form of special development package are given to the backward`
  line `areas of that State.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government shall, while considering the special development package for the`
  line `successor State of Andhra Pradesh, provide adequate incentives, in particular for Rayalaseema and north`
  line `coastal regions of that State.`
  line `PART VI`
  line `A PPORTIONMENT OF ASSETS AND LIABILITIES`
  line `47. Application of Part. –– ( 1 ) The provisions of this Part shall apply in relation to the apportionment`
  line `of the assets and liabilities of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh immediately before the appointed day.`
  line `( 2 ) The successor States shall be entitled to receive benefits arising out of the decisions taken by the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Pradesh and the successor States shall be liable tobear the financial liabilities`
  line `arising out of the decisions taken by the existing State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `( 3 ) The apportionment of assets and liabilities shall be subject to such financial adjustment as may be`
  line `necessary to secure just, reasonable and equitable apportionment ofthe assets and liabilities amongst the`
  line `successor States.`
  line `( 4 ) Any dispute regarding the amount of financial assets and liabilities shall be settled through mutual`
  line `agreement, failing which by order by the Central Government on the adviceof the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor - General of India.`
  line `48. Land and goods. –– ( 1 ) Subject to the other provisions of this Part, all land and all stores, articles`
  line `andother goods belonging to the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall, —`
  line `( a ) if within the transferred territory, pass to the State of Telangana; or`
  line `( b ) in any other case, remain the property of the State of Andhra Pradesh:`
  line `Provided that in case of properties situated outside the existing State of Andhra Pradesh, such`
  line `properties shall be apportioned between the successor States onthe basis of population ratio:`
  line `Provided further that where the Central Government is of opinion that any goods or class of goods`
  line `should be distributed among the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, otherwise than according to the`
  line `situation of the goods, the Central Government may issue such directions as it thinks fit for a just and`
  line `equitable distribution of the goods and the goods shall pass to the successor States accordingly:`
  line `Provided also that in case of any dispute relating to the distribution of any goods or class of goods`
  line `under this sub - section, the Central Government shall endeavour to settle such dispute through mutual`
  line `agreement arrived at between the Governments of the successor States for that purpose, failing which the`
  line `Central Government may, on request by any of the Governments of the successor States, after consulting`
  line `the Governments of the successor States, issue such direction as it may deem fit for the distribution of`
  line `such goods or class of goods, as the case may be, under this sub - section.`
  line `( 2 ) Stores held for specific purposes, such as use or utilisation in particular institutions, workshops or`
  line `undertakings or on particular works under construction, shall pass to the successor States in whose`
  line `territories such institutions, workshops, undertakings or works are located.`
  line `( 3 ) Stores relating to the Secretariat and offices of Heads of Departments having jurisdiction over the`
  line `whole of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall be divided betweenthe successor States on the basis of`
  line `population ratio.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-18
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Page 18`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  sourcePage 18
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line `( 4 ) In this section, the expression “land” includes immovable property of every kindand any rights in`
  line `or over such property, and the expression “goods” does not includecoins, bank notes and currency notes.`
  line `49. Treasury and bank balances. –– The total of the cash balances in all treasuries of the existing`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh and the credit balances of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh with the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India, the State Bank of India or any other bank immediately before the appointed day shall be`
  line `divided between the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana onthe basis of population ratio:`
  line `Provided that for the purposes of such division, there shall be no transfer of cash balances from any`
  line `treasury to any other treasury and the apportionment shall be effected by adjusting the credit balances of`
  line `the two States in the books of the Reserve Bank of India on the appointed d ay:`
  line `Provided further that if the State of Telangana has no account on the appointed day with the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India, the adjustment shall be made in such manner as the Central Government may, by order,`
  line direct.
  line `50. Arrears of taxes. –– The right to recover arrears of the tax or duty on property, including arrears of`
  line `land revenue, shall belong to the successor State in which the property is situated, and the right to recover`
  line `arrears of any other tax or duty shall belong to the successor State in whose territories the place of`
  line `assessment of that tax or duty is included on the appointed day.`
  line `51. Right to recover loans and advances. –– ( 1 ) The right of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh to`
  line `recover any loans oradvances made before the appointed day to any local body, society, agriculturist or`
  line `other person in an area within that State shall belong to the successor State in which that area is included`
  line `on that day.`
  line `( 2 ) The right of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh to recover any loans or advances made before`
  line `the appointed day to any person or institution outside that State shall belong to the State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh:`
  line `Provided that any sum recovered in respect of any such loan or advance shall be divided between the`
  line `States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana on the basis of population ratio.`
  line `52. Investments and credits in certain funds. –– ( 1 ) The securities held in respect of the investments`
  line `made from Cash Balances Investment Account or from any Fund in the Public Account of the existing`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh as specified in the Seventh Schedule shall be apportioned on the basis of`
  line `population ratio of the successor States:`
  line `Provided that the securities held in investments made from the Calamity Relief Fund of the existing`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh shall be divided in the ratio of the area of the territories occupied by the`
  line `successor States.`
  line `( 2 ) The investments of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh immediately before the appointed day in`
  line `any special fund, the objects of which are confined to a local area, shall belong to the State in which that`
  line `area is included on the appointed day:`
  line `Provided that the investments in such special funds on multiple entities situated indifferent parts of`
  line `the existing State, and such parts fall within the territories of the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana,`
  line `shall be apportioned between the successor States on the basis of population ratio.`
  line `( 3 ) The investments of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh immediately before the appointed day in`
  line `any private, commercial or industrial undertaking, the objects of which are confined to a local area, shall`
  line `belong to the successor State in which such area is included on the appointed day:`
  line `Provided that investments in such entities, having multiple units situated in different parts of the`
  line `existing State, and such parts fall within the territories of the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana,`
  line `shall be apportioned between the successor States on the basis of population ratio.`
  line `( 4 ) Where any body corporate constituted under a Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act for the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Pradesh or any part thereof has, by virtue of the provisions of Part II, become an`
  line `inter - State body corporate, the investments in, or loans oradvances to, any such body corporate by the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Pradesh made beforethe appointed day shall, save as otherwise expressly`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-19
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Page 19`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  sourcePage 19
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line 19
  line `provided by or under this Act, be divided between the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana in the`
  line `same proportion in which the assets of the body corporate are divided under the provisions of this Part.`
  line `53. Assets and liabilities of State undertakings. –– ( 1 ) The assets and liabilities relating to any`
  line `commercial or industrial undertaking of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh, where such undertaking or`
  line `part thereof is exclusively located in, or its operations are confined to, a local area, shall pass to the State`
  line `in which that area is included on the appointed day, irrespective of the location of its headquarters:`
  line `Provided that where the operation of such undertaking becomes inter - State by virtue of the provisions`
  line `of Part II, the assets and liabilities of ––`
  line `( a ) the operational units of the undertaking shall be apportioned between the two successor States`
  line `on location basis; and`
  line `( b ) the headquarters of such undertaking shall be apportioned between the two successor States on`
  line `the basis of population ratio.`
  line `( 2 ) Upon apportionment of the assets and liabilities, such assets and liabilities shall be transferred in`
  line `physical form on mutual agreement or by making payment or adjustment through any other mode as may`
  line `be agreed to by the successor States.`
  line `54. Public Debt. –– ( 1 ) All liabilities on account of Public Debt and Public Account of the existing`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh outstanding immediately before the appointed day shall be apportioned on the`
  line `basis of population ratio of the successor States unless a different mode of apportionment is provided`
  line `under the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The individual items of liabilities to be allocated to the successor States and the amount of`
  line `contribution required to be made by one successor State to another shall be such as may be ordered by the`
  line `Central Government on the advice of the Comptroller and Auditor - General of India:`
  line `Provided that till such orders are issued, the liabilities on account of Public Debt and Public Account`
  line `of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall continue to be the liabilities ofthe successor State of Andhra`
  line Pradesh.
  line `( 3 ) The liability on account of loan raised from any source and re - lent by the existing State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh to such entities as may be specified by the Central Government and whose area of operation is`
  line `confined to either of the successor States shall devolve on the respective States as specified in`
  line `sub - section ( 4 ).`
  line `( 4 ) The public debt of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh attributable to loan taken from any source`
  line `for the express purpose of re - lending the same to a specific institution and outstanding immediately before`
  line `the appointed day shall, —`
  line `( a ) if re - lent to any local body, body corporate or other institution in any local area, be the debt of`
  line `the State in which the local area is included on the appointed day; o r`
  line `( b ) if re - lent to any other corporation or institution which becomes an inter - State corporation or`
  line `institution on the appointed day, be divided between the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana in`
  line `the same proportion in which the assets of such body corporate or institution are divided under the`
  line `provisions of Part VII.`
  line `( 5 ) Where a sinking fund or a depreciation fund is maintained by the existing State of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `for repayment of any loan raised by it, the securities held in respect of investments made from that fund`
  line `shall be divided between the successor States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana in the same proportion in`
  line `which the total public debt is divided between the two States under this section.`
  line `( 6 ) In this section, the expression “Government security” means a security createdand issued by a`
  line `State Government for the purpose of raising a public loan and having any of the forms spe cified in, or`
  line `prescribed under, clause ( 2 ) of section 2 of the Public Debt Act, 1944 (18 of 1944).`
  line `55. Floating Debt. — All liabilities of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh in respect of any floating`
  line `loan to provide short term finance to any local body, body corporate or other institution, shall be`
  line `determined on the following basis, namely: ––`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-20
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Page 20`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  sourcePage 20
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `( a ) if, the purposes of the floating loan are, on and from the appointed day, exclusive purposes of`
  line `either of the successor States, then, of that State;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, it shall be divided on the basis of population ratio.`
  line `56. Refund of taxes collected in excess. — ( 1 ) The liability of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh to`
  line `refund any tax or duty on property, including land revenue, collected inexcess shall be the liability of the`
  line `successor State in whose territories the property is situated, and the liability of the existing State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh to refund any other tax or duty collected inexcess shall be apportioned between the`
  line `Successor States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana onthe basis of population ratio and the State`
  line `discharging the liability shall be entitled to receive from the other Stateits share of the liability, if any.`
  line `( 2 ) The liability of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh to refund any other tax or duty collected in`
  line `excess on the appointed day shall be the liability of the successor State in whose territories the place of`
  line `assessment of such tax or duty is included, and the liability of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh to`
  line `refund any other tax or duty collected in excess shall be apportioned between the Successor States of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh and Telangana on the basis of population ratio and the State discharging the li ability shall`
  line `be entitled to receive from the other State its share of the liability, if any.`
  line `57. Deposits, etc. — ( 1 ) The liability of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh inrespect of any civil`
  line `deposit or local fund deposit shall, as from the appointed day, be the liability of the successor State in`
  line `whose area the deposit has been made.`
  line `( 2 ) The liability of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh in respect of any charitable or other`
  line `endowment shall, as from the appointed day, be the liability of the successor State in whose area the`
  line `institution entitled to the benefit of the endowment is located or of the successor State to which the`
  line `objects of the endowment, under the terms thereof, are confined:`
  line `Provided that any civil deposits or loan funds or charitable or other endowment fund maintained by`
  line `the existing State of Andhra Pradesh before the appointed day having jurisdiction over the entire State`
  line `shall be apportioned between the successor States on thebasis of population ratio.`
  line `58. Provident Fund. — The liability of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh inrespect of the Provident`
  line `Fund account of a Government servant in service on the appointed day shall, as from that day, be the`
  line `liability of the successor State to which that Government servant is permanently allotted.`
  line `59. Pensions. — The liability of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh in respect of pensions shall pass`
  line `to, or be apportioned between, the successor States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana in accordance with`
  line `the provisions contained in the Eighth Schedule to this Act.`
  line `60. Contracts. — ( 1 ) Where, before the appointed day, the existing State of Andhra Pradesh has made`
  line `any contract in the exercise of its executive power for any purposes of the State, that contract shall, ––`
  line `( a ) if the purposes of the contract are, on and from the appointed day, exclusive purposes of`
  line `either of the successor States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, then it shall be deemed to have been`
  line `made in exercise of the executive power of that State and the liability shall be discharged by that`
  line `State; and`
  line `( b ) in any other case, all rights and liabilities which have accrued or may accrue under any such`
  line `contract shall be apportioned between the successor States on the basis of population ratio or in any`
  line `other manner as may be agreed to by the successor States.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of this section, there shall be deemed to be included in the liabilities which have`
  line `accrued or may accrue under any contract ––`
  line `( a ) any liability to satisfy an order or award made by any court or other tribunal in proceedings`
  line `relating to the contract; and`
  line `( b ) any liability in respect of expenses incurred in or in connection with any such proceedings.`
  line `( 3 ) This section shall have effect subject to the other provisions of this Part relating to the`
  line `apportionment of liabilities in respect of loans, guarantees and other financial obligations; and the bank`
  line `balances and securities shall, notwithstanding that they partake of the nature of contractual rights, be`
  line `dealt with under those provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-21
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Page 21`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  sourcePage 21
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `61. Liability in respect of actionable wrong. — Where, immediately before the appointed day, the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Prades his subject to any liability in respect of any actionable wrong other than`
  line `breach of contract, that liability shall, ––`
  line `( a ) if the cause of action arose wholly within the territories which, as from that day, are the`
  line `territories of either of the successor States of Andhra Pradesh or Telangana, be the liability of that`
  line `State; and`
  line `( b ) in any other case, be apportioned between the successor States on the basis of population ratio`
  line `or in any other manner as may be agreed to by the successor States.`
  line `62. Liability as guarantor. — Where, immediately before the appointed day, the existing State of`
  line `Andhra Pradeshis liable as guarantor in respect of any liability of a registered co - operative society or`
  line `other person, that liability shall, —`
  line `( a ) if the area of operations of such society or persons is confined to the territories which, as from`
  line `that day, are the territories of either of the States of Andhra Pradesh or Telangana, be a liability of that`
  line `State; and`
  line `( b ) in any other case, be apportioned between the successor States on the basis of population ratio`
  line `or in any other manner as may be agreed to by the successor States.`
  line `63. Items in suspense. — If any item in suspense is ultimately found to affect an asset or liability of`
  line `the nature referred to in any of the foregoing provisions of this Part, it shall be dealt with in accordance`
  line `with that provision.`
  line `64. Residuary provision. — The benefit or burden of any asset or liability of the existing State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh not dealt with in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall pass to the State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh in the first instance, subject to such financial adjustment as may be agreed upon between the`
  line `States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana or, in default of such agreement,as the Central Government may,`
  line `by order, direct.`
  line `65. Apportionment of assets or liabilities by agreement. — Where the successor States of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh and Telangana agree that the benefit or burden of any particular asset or liability should be`
  line `apportioned between them in a manner other than that provided for in the foregoing provisions of this`
  line `Part, notwithstanding anything contained therein, the benefit or burden of that asset or liability shall be`
  line `apportioned in the manner agreed upon.`
  line `66. Power of Central Government to order allocation or adjustment in certain cases. — Where,`
  line `by virtue of any of the provisions of this Part, either of the successor States of Andhra Pradesh and`
  line `Telangana becomes entitled to any property or obtains any benefits or becomes subject to any liability,`
  line `and the Central Government is of opinion, on a reference made within a period of three years from the`
  line `appointed day by either of the States, that it is just and equitable that such property or those benefits`
  line `should be transferred to, or shared with, the other successor State, or that a contribution towards that`
  line `liability should be made by the other successor State, the said property or benefits shall be allocated in`
  line `such manner between the two States, or the other State shall make to the State subject to the liability such`
  line `contribution in respect thereof, as the Central Government may, after consultation with the two State`
  line `Governments, by order, determine.`
  line `67. Certain expenditure to be charged on Consolidated Fund. — All sums payable by the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or by the State of Telangana, as the case may be, to the other State, or by the Central`
  line `Government to the successor States, by virtue of the provisions of this Act, shall be charged on the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of the State by which such sums are payable or, as the case may be, the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India.`
  line `PART VII`
  line `P ROVISIONS AS TO CERTAIN CORPORATIONS`
  line `68. Provisions for various companies and corporations. — ( 1 ) The companies and corporations`
  line `specified in the Ninth Schedule constituted for the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall, on and from the`
  line `appointed day, continue to function in those areas in respect of which they were functioning immediately`
  line `before that day, subject to the provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-22
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Page 22`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  sourcePage 22
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line 22
  line `( 2 ) The assets, rights and liabilities of the companies and corporations referred to in sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `shall be apportioned between the successor States in the manner provided in section 53.`
  line `69. Continuance of arrangements in regard to generation and supply of electric power and`
  line `supply of water. — If it appears to the Central Government that the arrangement in regard to the`
  line `generation or supply of electric power or the supply of water for any area or in regard to the execution of`
  line `any project for such generation or supply has been or is likely to be modified to the disadvantage of that`
  line `area by reason of the fact that it is, by virtue of the provisions of Part II, outside the State in which the`
  line `pow er stations and other installations for the generation and supply of such power, or the catchment area,`
  line `reservoirs and other works for the supply of water, as the case may be, are located, the Central`
  line `Government may, after consultation with the Governments of the successor States wherever necessary,`
  line `give such directions as it deems proper to the State Government or other authority concerned for the`
  line `maintenance, so far as practicable, of the previous arrangement and the State to which such directions are`
  line `giv en shall comply with them.`
  line `70. Provisions as to Andhra Pradesh State Financial Corporation. — ( 1 ) The Andhra Pradesh State`
  line `Financial Corporation established under the State Financial Corporations Act, 195 1 (63 of 1951) shall, on`
  line `and from the appointed day, continue to functionin those areas in respect of which it was functioning`
  line `immediately before that day, subject tothe provisions of this section and to such directions as may, from`
  line `time to time, be issued by the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub - section ( 1 ) in respect of the`
  line `Corporation may include a direction that the said Act, in its application to the Corporation, shall have`
  line `effect subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be specified in the direction.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ), the Board of Directors`
  line `of the Corporation may, with the previous approval of the Central Government and shall, if so required by`
  line `the Central Government, convene at any time after the appointed day a meeting for the consideration of a`
  line `scheme for the reconstitution or reorganisation or dissolution, as the case may be, of the Corporation,`
  line `including proposals regarding the formation of new Corporations, and the transfer thereto of the assets,`
  line `rights and liabilities of the existing Corporation, and if such a scheme is approved at the general meeting`
  line `by a resolution passed bya majority of the share holders present and voting, the scheme shall be submitted`
  line `to the Central Government for its sanction.`
  line `( 4 ) If the scheme is sanctioned by the Central Government either without modifications or with`
  line `modifications which are approved at a general meeting, the Central Government shall certify the scheme,`
  line `and upon such certification, the scheme shall, notwithstanding any thing to the contrary contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, be binding on the Corporations affected by the scheme as well as the`
  line `shareholders and creditors thereof.`
  line `( 5 ) If the scheme is not so approved or sanctioned, the Central Government may refer the scheme to`
  line `such Judge of the High Court of Andhra Pradesh or the High Court of Telangana as may be nominated in`
  line `this behalf by the Chief Justice thereof, and the decision of the Judge inregard to the scheme shall be final`
  line `and shall be binding on the Corporations affected by the scheme as well as the shareholders and creditors`
  line thereof.
  line `( 6 ) Nothing in the preceding provisions of this section shall be construed as preventing the`
  line `Government of the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana from constituting, at anytime on or after the`
  line `appointed day, a State Financial Corporation for that State under the State Financial Corporations Act,`
  line `1951 (63 of 1951).`
  line `71. Certain provisions for companies. — Notwithstanding anything in this Part, the Central`
  line `Government may, for each of the companies specified in the Ninth Schedule to this Act, issue direc tions –`
  line `( a ) regarding the division of the interests and shares of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh in the`
  line `Company between the successor States;`
  line `( b ) requiring the reconstitution of the Board of Directors of the Company so as to give adequate`
  line `representation to the successor States.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-23
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Page 23`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  sourcePage 23
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `72. Temporary provisions as to continuance of certain existing road transport permits. — ( 1 )`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 88 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988), a`
  line `permit granted by the State Transport Authority of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh or any Regional`
  line `Transport Authority in that State shall, if such permit was, immediately before the appointed day, valid`
  line `and effective in any area in the transferred territory, be deemed to continue to be valid and effective in`
  line `that are a after that day till its period of validity subject to the provisions of that Act as for the time being`
  line `in force in that area; and it shall not be necessary for any such permit to be countersigned by the State`
  line `Transport Authority of Telangana or any Regional Transport Authority therein for the purpose of`
  line `validating it for use in such area:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the successor State Government or`
  line `Governments concerned add to amend or vary the conditions attached to the permit by the Authority by`
  line `which the permit was granted.`
  line `( 2 ) No tolls, entrance fees or other charges of a like nature shall be levied after the appointed day in`
  line `respect of any transport vehicle for its operations in any of the successor States under any such permit, if`
  line `such vehicle was, immediately before that day, exempt from the payment of any such toll, entrance fees`
  line `or other charges for its operations in the transferred territory:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the State Government or`
  line `Governments concerned, authorise the levy of any such toll, entrance fees or other charges, as the case`
  line `may be:`
  line `Provided further that the provisions of this sub - section shall not be applicable where any such tolls,`
  line `entrance fees or other charges of a like nature are leviable for the use of any road or bridge which is`
  line `constructed or developed for commercial purpose by the State Government, an undertaking of the State`
  line `Government, a joint undertaking in which the State Government is a shareholder or the private sector.`
  line `73. Special provisions relating to, retrenchment compensation in certain cases. — Where on`
  line `account of the reorganisation of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh under this Act, any body corporate`
  line `constituted under a Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act, any co - operative society registered under`
  line `any law relating to co - operative societies or any commercial or industrial undertaking of that State is`
  line `reconstituted or reorganised in any manner whatsoever or is amalgamated with any other body corporate,`
  line `co - oper ative society or undertaking, or is dissolved, and in consequence of such reconstitution,`
  line `reorganisation, amalgamation or dissolution, any workman employed by such body corporate or in any`
  line `such co - operative societyor undertaking, is transferred to, or re - employed by, any other body corporate,`
  line `or in any other co - operative society or undertaking, then, notwithstanding anything contained in section`
  line `25F or section 25FF or section 25FFF of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), such transfer or`
  line `re - emplo yment shall not entitle him to any compensation under that section:`
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( a ) the terms and conditions of service applicable to the workman after suchtransfer or`
  line `re - employment are not less favourable to the workman than those applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the transfer or re - employment;`
  line `( b ) the employer in relation to the body corporate, the co - operative society orthe undertaking`
  line `where the workman transferred or re - employed is, by agreement or otherwise, legally liable to pay to`
  line `the workman, in the event of his retrenchment, compensation undersection 25F or section 25FF or`
  line `section 25FFF of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) on the basis that his service has been`
  line `continuous and has not been interrupted by the transfer or re - employment.`
  line `74. Special provision as to income - tax. — Where the assets, rights and liabilities of any body`
  line `corporate carrying on business are, under the provisions of this Part, transferred to any other bodies`
  line `corporate which after the transfer carry on the same business, the losses or profits or gains sustained by`
  line `the body corporate first - mentioned which, but for such transfer, would have been allowed to be carried`
  line `forward and set off in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VI of the Income - tax Act, 1961 (43 of`
  line `196 1), shall be apportioned amongst the transferee bodies corporate in accordance with the rules to be`
  line `made by the Central Government in this behalf and, upon such apportionment, the share of loss allotted to`
  line `each transferee body corporate shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VI of the`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-24
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Page 24`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  sourcePage 24
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line 24
  line `said Act, as if the transferee body corporate had itself sustained such loss in a business carried on by it in`
  line `the years in which those losses were sustained.`
  line `75. Continuance of facilities in certain State institutions. — ( 1 ) The Government of the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or the State of Telangana, as the case may be, shall, in respect of the institutions specified`
  line `in the Tenth Schedule to this Act, located in that State, continue to provide facilities to the people of the`
  line `other State which shall not, in any respect, be less favourable to such people than what were being`
  line `provided to them before the appointed day, for such period and upon such terms and conditions as may be`
  line `agreed upon between the two State Governments within a period of one year from the appointed day or, if`
  line `no agreement is reached within the said period, as may be fixed by order of the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may, at any time within one year from the appointed day, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, specify in the Tenth Schedule referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) any other institution`
  line `existing on the appointed day in the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana and, on the issue of such`
  line `notification, such Schedule shall bedeemed to be amended by the inclusion of the said institution therein.`
  line `PART VIII`
  line `P ROVISIONS AS TO SERVICES`
  line `76. Provisions relating to All - India Services. — ( 1 ) In this section, the expression “State cadre” ––`
  line `( a ) in relation to the Indian Administrative Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian`
  line `Administrative Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954;`
  line `( b ) in relation to the Indian Police Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Police`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954; and`
  line `( c ) in relation to the Indian Forest Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Forest`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1966.`
  line `( 2 ) In place of the cadres of the Indian Administrative Service, Indian Police Serviceand Indian Forest`
  line `Service for the existing State of Andhra Pradesh, there shall, on and from the appointed day, be two`
  line `separate cadres, one for the State of Andhra Pradesh and the other for the State of Telangana in respect`
  line `of each of these services.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisional strength, composition and allocation of officers to the State cadres referred to in`
  line `sub - section ( 2 ) shall be such as the Central Government may, by order, determine on or after the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line `( 4 ) The members of each of the said services borne on the Andhra Pradesh cadre immediately before`
  line `the appointed day shall be allocated to the successor State cadres of the same service constituted under`
  line `sub - section ( 2 ) in such manner and with effect from such date or dates as the Central Government may,`
  line `by order, specify.`
  line `( 5 ) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the operation, on or after the appointed day, of`
  line `the All - India Services Act, 1951 (61 of 1951), or the rules made thereunder.`
  line `77. Provisions relating to other services. — ( 1 ) Every person who immediately before the appointed`
  line `day is serving on substantive basis in connection with the affairs of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `shall, on and from that day provisionally continue to serve in connection with the affairs of the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh unless he is required, by general or special order of the Central Government to serve`
  line `provisionally in connection with the affairs of the State of Telangana:`
  line `Provided that every direction under this sub - section issued after the expiry of a period of one year`
  line `from the appointed day shall be issued with the consultation of the Governments of the successor States.`
  line `( 2 ) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Central Government shall, by general or special`
  line `order, determine the successor State to which every person referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) shall be finally`
  line `allotted for service, after consideration of option received by seeking option from the employees, and the`
  line `date with effect from which such allotment shall take effect or be deemed to have taken effect:`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-25
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Page 25`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  sourcePage 25
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line 25
  line `Provided that even after the allocation has been made, the Central Government may, in order to meet`
  line `any deficiency in the service, depute officers of other State services from one successor State to the`
  line `other:`
  line `Provided further that as far as local, district, zonal and multi - zonal cadres are concerned, the`
  line `employees shall continue to serve, on or after the appointed day, in that cadre:`
  line `Provided also that the employees of local, district, zonal and multi - zonal cadres which fall entirely in`
  line `one of the successor States, shall be deemed to be allotted to that successor State:`
  line `Provided also that if a particular zone or multi - zone falls in both the successor States, then the`
  line `employees of such zonal or multi - zonal cadre shall be finally allotted to one or the other successor States`
  line `in terms of the provisions of this sub - section.`
  line `( 3 ) Every person who is finally allotted under the provisions of sub - section ( 2 ) to asuccessor State`
  line `shall, if he is not already serving therein, be made available for serving in the successor State from such`
  line `date as may be agreed upon between the Governments of the successor States or, in default of such`
  line `agreement, as may be determined by the Central Government:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall have the power to review any of its orders issued under`
  line `this section.`
  line `78. Other provisions relating to services. — ( 1 ) Nothing in this section or insection 77 shall be`
  line `deemed to affect, on or after the appointed day, the operation of theprovisions of Chapter I of Part XIV of`
  line `the Constitutionin relation to determination of the conditions of service of persons serving in`
  line `connectionwith the affairs of the Union or any State:`
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day in the case of`
  line `any person deemed to have been allocated to the State of Andhra Pradesh or to the State of Telangana`
  line `under section 77 shall not be varied to his disadvantage except with the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government.
  line `( 2 ) All services prior to the appointed day rendered by a person, —`
  line `( a ) if he is deemed to have been allocated to any State under section 77, shall be deemed to have`
  line `been rendered in connection with the affairs of that State;`
  line `( b ) if he is deemed to have been allocated to the Union in connection with the administration of`
  line `the successor State of Telangana, shall be deemed to have been rendered in connection with the`
  line `affairs of the Union, for the purposes of the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of section 77 shall not apply in relation to members of any All - India Service.`
  line `79. Provisions as to continuance of officers in same post. — Every person who, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in connection with the affairs`
  line `of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh in any area which on that day falls within one of the successor`
  line `States shall continue to hold the same post or office in that successor State, and shall be deemed, on and`
  line `from that day, to have been duly appointed to the post or office by the Government of, or other`
  line `appropriate authority in, that successor State:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a competent authority, on and from`
  line `the appointed day, from passing in relation to such person any order affecting the continuance in such post`
  line `or office.`
  line `80. Advisory committees. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by order, establish one or more`
  line `Advisory Committees, within a period of thirty days from the date of enactment of the Andhra Pradesh`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 2014, for the purpose of assisting it in regard to ––`
  line `( a ) the discharge of any of its functions under this Part; and`
  line `( b ) the ensuring of fair and equitable treatment to all persons affected by the provisions of this`
  line `Part and the proper consideration of any representations made by such persons.`
  line `( 2 ) The allocation guidelines shall be issued by the Central Government on or after the date of`
  line `enactment of the Andhra Pradesh Reorganisation Act, 2014 and the actual allocation of individual`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-26
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Page 26`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  sourcePage 26
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line 26
  line `employees shall be made by the Central Government on the recommendations of the Advisory`
  line `Committee:`
  line `Provided that in case of disagreement or conflict of opinion, the decision of the Central Government`
  line `shall be final:`
  line `Provided further that necessary guidelines as and when required shall be framed by the Central`
  line `Government or as the case may be, by the State Advisory Committee which shall be approved by the`
  line `Central Government before such guidelines are issued.`
  line `81. Power of Central Government to give directions. — The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions to the State Government of Andhra Pradesh and the State Government of Telangana as may`
  line `appear to it to be necessary for the purpose of giving effect to the foregoing provisions of this Part and the`
  line `State Governments shall comply with such directions.`
  line `82. Provision for employees of Public Sector Undertakings, etc. — On and from the appointed day,`
  line `the employees of State Public Sector Undertakings, corporations and other autonomous bodies shall`
  line `continue to function in such undertaking, corporation or autonomous bodies for a period of one year and`
  line `during this period the corporate body concerned shall determine the modalities for distributing the`
  line `personnel between the two successor States.`
  line `83. Provisions as to State Public Service Commission. — ( 1 ) The Public Service Commission for the`
  line `existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall, on and from the appointed day, be the Public Service Commission`
  line `for the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `( 2 ) There shall be constituted a Public Service Commission in accordance with article 315 of the`
  line `Constitution by the successor State of Telangana, and until such Commissionis constituted, the Union`
  line `Public Service Commission may, with the approval of the President, agree to serve the needs of the State`
  line `of Telangana in terms of clause ( 4 ) of that article.`
  line `( 3 ) The persons holding office immediately before the appointed day as the Chairman or other`
  line `member of the Public Service Commission for the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall, as from the`
  line `appointed day, be the Chairman or, as the case may be, the other memberof the Public Service`
  line `Commission for the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `( 4 ) Every person who becomes the Chairman or other member of the Public ServiceCommission for`
  line `the State of Andhra Pradesh on the appointed day under sub - section ( 3 ) shall ––`
  line `( a ) be entitled to receive from the Government of the State of Andhra Pradesh conditions of`
  line `service not less favourable than those to which he was entitled under the provisions applicable to him;`
  line `( b ) subject to the proviso to clause ( 2 ) of article 316, hold office orcontinue to hold office until`
  line `the expiration of his term of office as determined under the provisions applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the appointed day.`
  line `( 5 ) The report of the Andhra Pradesh Public Service Commission as to the work done by the`
  line `Commission in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be presented under clause ( 2 ) of`
  line `article 323 to the Governors of the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana and the Governor of the State`
  line `of Andhra Pradesh shall, on receipt of such report, cause a copy thereof together with a memorandum`
  line `explaining as far as possible, as respects thecases, if any, where the advice of the Commission was not`
  line `accepted, t he reasons for such non - acceptance to be laid before the Legislature of the State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh and it shall not be necessary to cause such report or any such memorandum to be laid before the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the State of Telangana.`
  line `PART IX`
  line `M ANAGEMENT A ND D EVELOPMENT O F W ATER R ESOURCES`
  line `84. Apex Council for Godavari and Krishna river water resources and their Management`
  line `Boards. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall, on and from the appointed day, constitute an Apex Cou ncil`
  line `for the supervision of the functioning of the Godavari River Management Board and Krishna River`
  line `Management Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-27
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Page 27`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  sourcePage 27
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line 27
  line `( 2 ) The Apex Council shall consist of –––`
  line `( a ) Minister of Water Resources, Government of India — Chairperson;`
  line `( b ) Chief Minister of State of Andhra Pradesh — Member;`
  line `( c ) Chief Minister of State of Telangana — Member.`
  line `( 3 ) The functions of the Apex Council shall include ––`
  line `( i ) supervision of the functioning of the Godavari River Management Board and Krishna River`
  line `Management Board;`
  line `( ii ) planning and approval of proposals for construction of new projects, if any, based on`
  line `Godavari or Krishna river water, after getting the proposal appraised and recommended by the River`
  line `Management Boards and by the Central Water Commission, wherever required;`
  line `( iii ) resolution of any dispute amicably arising out of the sharing of river waters through`
  line `negotiations and mutual agreement between the successor States;`
  line `( iv ) reference of any disputes not covered under Krishna Water Disputes Tribunal, to a Tribunal`
  line `to be constituted under the Inter - State River Water DisputesAct, 1956 (33 of 1956).`
  line `85. Constitution and functions of River Management Board. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall`
  line `constitute two separate Boards to be called the Godavari River Management Board and Krishna River`
  line `Management Board (to be known as the Board), within a period of sixty days from the appointed day, for`
  line `the administration, regulation, maintenance and operation of such projects, as may be notified by the`
  line `CentralGovernment from time to time.`
  line `( 2 ) The headquarters of Godavari River Management Board shall be located in the successor State of`
  line `Telangana and of the Krishna River Management Board shall be located in the successor State of Andhra`
  line Pradesh.
  line `( 3 ) The Godavari River Management Board and Krishna River Management Board shall be`
  line `autonomous bodies under the administrative control of the Central Government, and shall comply with`
  line `such directions as may, from time to time, be given to them by the Central Government.`
  line `( 4 ) Each Board shall consist of the following Chairperson and Members, namely: ––`
  line '` ( a ) a Chairperson not below the rank or level of Secretary or Additional Secretary to the'
  line `Government of India to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line `( b ) two members, to be nominated by each of the successor States, of which one shall be the`
  line `technical member not below the rank of Chief Engineer and the other administrative member to`
  line `represent the concerned States;`
  line `( c ) one expert to be nominated by the Central Government.`
  line `( 5 ) Each Board shall have a full - time Member Secretary, not below the rank of Chief Engineer in the`
  line `Central Water Commission, to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line `( 6 ) The Central Government shall create such number of posts of the rank of Chief Engineer in the`
  line `Central Water Commission, as it considers necessary.`
  line `( 7 ) Each Board shall be assisted in the day to day management of reservoirs by the Central Industrial`
  line `Security Force constituted under the Central Industrial Security Force Act, 1968 (50 of 1968 ), on such`
  line `terms and conditions as the Central Government may specify.`
  line `( 8 ) The functions of each Board shall include ––`
  line `( a ) the regulation of supply of water from the projects to the successor States having regard to ––`
  line `( i ) awards granted by the Tribunals constituted under the Inter - State River Water Disputes`
  line `Act, 1956 (33 of 1956 );`
  line `( ii ) any agreement entered into or arrangement made covering the Government of existing`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh and any other State or Union territory;`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-28
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Page 28`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  sourcePage 28
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line 28
  line `( b ) the regulation of supply of power generated to the authority in - charge ofthe distribution of`
  line `power having regard to any agreement entered into or arrangement made covering the Government of`
  line `the existing State of Andhra Pradesh and any other State or Union territory;`
  line `( c ) the construction of such of the remaining on - going or new works connected with the`
  line `development of the water resources projects relating to the rivers or their tributaries through the`
  line `successor States as the Central Government may specify by notification in the Official Gazette;`
  line `( d ) making an appraisal of any proposal for construction of new projects on Godavari or Krishna`
  line `rivers and giving technical clearance, after satisfying that such projects do not negatively impact the`
  line `availability of water as per the awards of the Tribunals constituted under the Inter - State River Water`
  line `Disputes Act, 1956 (33 of 1956 ) for the projects already completed or taken up before the appointed`
  line `day; and`
  line `( e ) such other functions as the Central Government may entrust to it on the basis of the principles`
  line `specified in the Eleventh Schedule.`
  line `86. Staff of the Management Board. –– ( 1 ) The Board shall employ such staff as it may consider`
  line `necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions under this Act and such staff shall, at the first`
  line `instance, be appointed on deputation from the successor States in equal proportion and absorbed`
  line `permanently in the Board.`
  line `( 2 ) The Government of the successor States shall at all times provide the necessary funds to the Board`
  line `to meet all expenses (including the salaries and allowances of the staff) required for the discharge of its`
  line `functions and such amounts shall be apportioned between the States concerned in such proportion as the`
  line `Central Government may, having regard to the benefits to each of the said States, specify.`
  line `( 3 ) The Board may delegate such of its powers, functions and duties as it may deem fit to the`
  line `Chairman of the said Board or to any officer subordinate to the Board.`
  line `( 4 ) The Central Government may, for the purpose of enabling the Board tofunctionefficiently, issue`
  line `such directions to the State Governments concerned, or any other authority, and the State Governments, or`
  line `the other authority, shall comply with such directions.`
  line `87. Jurisdiction of Board. –– ( 1 ) The Board shall ordinarily exercise jurisdiction on Godavari and`
  line `Krishna riversin regard to any of the projects over headworks (barrages, dams, reservoirs, regulating`
  line `structures), part of canal network and transmission lines necessary to deliver water orpower to the States`
  line `concerned, as may be notified by the Central Government, having regard to the awards, if any, made by`
  line `the Tribunals constituted under the Inter - State River Water Disputes Act, 1956 (33 of 1956 ).`
  line `( 2 ) If any question arises as to whether the Board has jurisdiction under sub - section ( 1 ) over any`
  line `project referred thereto, the same shall be referred to the Central Government for decision thereon.`
  line `88. Power of Board to make regulations. –– The Board may make regulations consistent with the Act`
  line `and the rules made thereunder, to provide for —`
  line `( a ) regulating the time and place of meetings of the Board and the procedure to be followed for`
  line `the transaction of business at such meetings;`
  line `( b ) delegation of powers and duties of the Chairman or any officer of the Board;`
  line `( c ) the appointment and regulation of the conditions of service of the officers and other staff of`
  line `the Board;`
  line `( d ) any other matter for which regulations are considered necessary by the Board.`
  line `89. Allocation of water resources. –– The term of the Krishna Water Disputes Tribunal shall be`
  line `extended with the following terms of reference, namely: ––`
  line `( a ) shall make project - wise specific allocation, if such allocation have not been made by a`
  line `Tribunal constituted under the Inter - State River Water Disputes Act, 1956 (33 of 1956 );`
  line `( b ) shall determine an operational protocol for project - wise release of water in the event of deficit`
  line flows.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-29
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Page 29`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  sourcePage 29
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line 29
  line `Explanation. –– For the purposes of this section, it is clarified that the project specific awards already`
  line `made by the Tribunal on or before the appointed day shall be binding on the successor States.`
  line `90. Polavaram Irrigation Project to be a national project. –– ( 1 ) The Polavaram Irrigation Project is`
  line `hereby declared to be a national project.`
  line `( 2 ) It is hereby declared that it is expedient in the public interest that the Union should take under its`
  line `control the regulation and development of the Polavaram Irrigation Project for the purposes of irrigation.`
  line `( 3 ) The consent for Polavaram Irrigation Project shall be deemed to have been given by the successor`
  line `State of Telangana.`
  line `( 4 ) The Central Government shall execute the project and obtain all requisite clearances including`
  line `environmental, forests, and rehabilitation and resettlement norms.`
  line `91. Arrangements on Tungabhadra Board. –– ( 1 ) The Governments of the successor States of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh and Telangana shall replace the existing State of Andhra Pradesh on the Tungabhadra`
  line Board.
  line `( 2 ) The Tungabhadra Board shall continue to monitor the release of water to High Level Canal, Low`
  line `Level Canal and Rajolibanda Diversion Scheme.`
  line `PART X`
  line `I NFRASTRUCTURE A ND S PECIAL E CONOMIC M EASURES`
  line `92. Successor States to follow principles, guidelines, etc., issued by Central Government. –– The`
  line `principles, guidelines, directions and orders issued by the Central Government,on and from the appointed`
  line `day, on matters relating to coal, oil and natural gas, and power generation, transmission and distribution`
  line `as enumerated in the Twelfth Schedule shall be implemented by the successor States.`
  line `93. Measures for progress and development of successor States. –– The Central Government shall`
  line `take all necessary measures as enumerated in the Thirteenth Schedule for the progress and sustainable`
  line `development of the successor States within a period of ten years from the a ppointed day.`
  line `94. Fiscal measures including tax incentives. –– ( 1 ) The Central Government shall take appropriate`
  line `fiscal measures, including offer of tax incentives, to the successor States, to promote industrialisation and`
  line `economic growth in both the States.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government shall support the programmes for the development of backward areas in`
  line `the successor States, including expansion of physical and social infrastructure.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government shall provide special financial support for the creation of essential`
  line `facilities in the new capital of the successor State of Andhra Pradesh includingthe Raj Bhawan, High`
  line `Court, Government Secretariat, Legislative Assembly, Legislative Council, and such other essential`
  line infrastructure.
  line `( 4 ) The Central Government shall facilitate the creation of a new capital for the successor State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh, if considered necessary, by denotifying degraded forest land.`
  line `PART XI`
  line `A CCESS TO HIGHER EDUCATION`
  line `95. Equal opportunities for quality higher education to all students. –– In order to ensure equal`
  line `opportunities for quality higher education to all studentsin the successor States, the existing admission`
  line `quotas in all government or private, aided orunaided, institutions of higher, technical and medical`
  line `education in so far as it is provided under article 371D of the Constitution, shall continue as such for a`
  line `period of ten years during which the existing common admission process shall continue.`
  line `PART XII`
  line `L EGAL A NDMISCELLANEOUS PROVISIONS`
  line `96. Amendment of article 168 of the Constitution. –– In sub - clause ( a ) of clause ( 1 ) of article 168 of`
  line `the Constitution, for the word “Tamil Nadu”, the words “Tamil Nadu, Telangana” shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-30
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Page 30`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  sourcePage 30
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line 30
  line `97. Amendment of article 371D of the Constitution. –– On and from the appointed day, in`
  line `article 371D of the Constitution, ––`
  line `( a ) in the marginal heading, for the words “the State of Andhra Pradesh”, the words “the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or the State of Telangana” shall be substituted;`
  line `( b ) for clause ( 1 ), the following clause shall be substituted, namely: ––`
  line `“( 1 ) The President may by order made with respect to the State of Andhra Pradesh or the`
  line `State of Telangana, provide, having regard to the requirement of each State, for equitable`
  line `opportunities and facilities for the people belonging to different parts of such State, in the matter`
  line `of public employment and in thematter of education, and different provisions may be made for`
  line `various parts of the States.”;`
  line `( c ) in clause ( 3 ), for the words “the State of Andhra Pradesh”, the words “the State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh and for the State of Telangana” shall be substituted.`
  line `98. Amendment of section 15A of Act 43 of 1951. –– In section 15A of the Representation of the`
  line `People Act, 1951, after the words and figures “under the Tamil Nadu Legislative Council Act, 2010`
  line `(16 of 2010 ) ”, the words and figures “and constituting the Legislative Council of the State of Telangana`
  line `under the Andhra Pradesh Reorganisation Act, 2014” shall be inserted.`
  line `99. Amendment of section 15 of Act 37 of 1956. –– On and from the appointed day, in section 15 of`
  line `the States Reorganisation Act,1956, in clause ( e ), for the words “Andhra Pradesh”, the words “Andhra`
  line `Pradesh and Telangana” shall be substituted.`
  line `100. Territorial extent of laws. –– The provisions of Part II shall not be deemed to have affected any`
  line `change in the territories to which the Andhra Pradesh Land Reforms (Ceiling on Agricultural Holdings)`
  line `Act, 1973 ( Andhra Pradesh Act No. 1 of 1973 ) and any other law in force immediately before the`
  line `appointed day extends orapplies, and territorial references in any such law to the State of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `shall, until otherwise provided by a competent Legislature or other competent authority be construedas`
  line `mean ing the territories within the existing State of Andhra Pradesh before the appointedday.`
  line `101. Power to adapt laws. –– For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or the State of Telangana of any law made before the appointed day, the appropriate`
  line `Government may, before the expiration of two years from that day, by order, make suchadaptations and`
  line `modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be necessary or expedient, and`
  line `thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations and modifications so made until`
  line `alte red, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other competent authority.`
  line `Explanation. –– In this section, the expression “appropriate Government” means as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List, the Central Government, and as respects any other law`
  line `in its application to a State, the State Government.`
  line `102. Power to construe laws. –– Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `madeunder section 10 2 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or`
  line `authority, required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose offacilitating its application in`
  line `relation to the State of Andhra Pradesh or the State of Telangana, construe the law in such manner,`
  line `without affecting the substance, as may be necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the cou rt,`
  line `tribunal or authority.`
  line `103. Power to name authorities, etc., for exercising statutory functions. – – The Government of the`
  line `State of Telangana, as respects the transferred territory may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify the authority, officer or person who, onor after the appointed day, shall be competent to exercise`
  line `such functions exercisable underany law in force on that day as may be mentioned in that notification and`
  line `such law shall have effect accordingly.`
  line `104. Legal proceedings. –– Where, immediately before the appointed day, the existing State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh is a party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities`
  line `subject to apportionment between the States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana under this Act, the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or the State of Telangana which succeeds to, or acquires a share in, that property or those`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-31
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Page 31`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  sourcePage 31
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line 31
  line `rights or liabilities by virtue of any provision of this Act shall be deemed to be substituted for the existing`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh or added as a party to those proceedings, and the proceedings may continue`
  line accordingly.
  line `105. Transfer of pending proceedings. –– ( 1 ) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before acourt (other than High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which on`
  line `that day falls within the State of Andhra Pradesh shall, if it is aproceeding relating exclusively to the`
  line `territory, which as from that day are the territories of the State of Telangana, stand transferred to the`
  line `corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer of that State.`
  line `( 2 ) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `it shall be referred to the High Court at Hyderabad and the decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line `( 3 ) In this section ––`
  line `( a ) “proceeding” includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line `( b ) “corresponding court, tribunal authority or officer” in the State of Telanganameans ––`
  line `( i ) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding would`
  line `have laid if it had been instituted after the appointed day; or`
  line `( ii ) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority, or officer in that State, as may be`
  line `determined after the appointed day by the Government of that State or the Central Government, as`
  line `the case may be, or before the appointed day by the Government of the existing State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer.`
  line `106. Right of pleaders to practise in certain cases. –– Any person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is enrolled as a pleader entitled to practise in any subordinate court in the existing State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh shall, for a period of one year from that day, continue to be entitled to practise in those`
  line `courts, notwithstanding that the whole or any part of the territories within the jurisdiction of those courts`
  line `has been transferred to the State of Telangana.`
  line `107. Effect of provisions of the Act inconsistent with other laws. –– The provisions of this Act shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent there with contained in any other law.`
  line `108. Power to remove difficulties. –– ( 1 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may, by order do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to`
  line `him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line `( 2 ) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
