obj_root_law_sections_60:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-60
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Page 60`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  sourcePage 60
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line 60
  line `T HE EIGHTH SCHEDULE`
  line `( See section 59)`
  line `APPORTIONMENT OF LIABILITY IN RESPECT OF PENSIONS`
  line `1. Subject to the adjustments mentioned in paragraph 3, each of the successor Statesshall, in respect of`
  line `pensionsgranted before the appointed day by the existing State ofAndhra Pradesh, pay the pensions drawn`
  line `in its treasuries.`
  line `2. Subject to the said adjustments, the liability in respect of pensions of officersserving in connection`
  line `with theaffairs of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh who retire orproceed on leave preparatory to`
  line `retirement before the appointed day, but whose claims forpensions are outstanding immediately before`
  line `that day, shall be the liability of the State ofAndhra Pradesh.`
  line `3. There shall be computed, in respect of the period commencing on the appointedday and ending on`
  line `such date after the appointed day, as may be fixed by the CentralGovernment and in respect of each`
  line `subsequent financial year, the total payments made tothe two successor States in respect of pensions`
  line `referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2. The totalrepresenting the liability of the existing State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh in respect of pensions andother retirement benefits shall be apportioned between the successor`
  line `States o n the basis ofpopulation ratio and any successor State paying more than its due share shall be`
  line `reimbursedthe excess amount by the other successor State paying less.`
  line `4. The liability of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh in respect of pension rollsgranted before the`
  line `appointed day and drawn in any area outside the territories of theexisting State shall be the liability of the`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh subject to adjustments tobe made in accordance with paragraph 3 as if such`
  line `pensions had been drawn in any treasuryin the State of Andhra Pradesh under paragraph 1.`
  line `5. (1) The liability in respect of the pension of any officer serving immediately beforethe appointed`
  line `day inconnection with the affairs of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh andretiring on or after that day,`
  line `shall be that of the successor State granting him the pensionand other retirement benefits; but the portion`
  line `of the pension and other retirement benefitsattributable to the service of any such officer before the`
  line `appointed day in connection withthe affairs of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall b e allocated`
  line `between the successorStates on the basis of population ratio, and the Government granting the pension`
  line `shall beentitled to receive from the other successor State its share of the liability.`
  line `(2) If any such officer was serving after the appointed day in connection with theaffairs of more than`
  line `one successor State other than the one granting the pension shallreimburse to the Government by which`
  line `the pension is granted an amount which bears to theportion of the pension attributable to his service after`
  line `the appointed day the same ratio asthe period of his qualifying service after the appointed day under the`
  line `reimbursing Statebears to the total qualifying service of such officer after the appointed da y reckoned for`
  line `thepurposes of pension.`
  line `6. Any reference in this Schedule to a pension shall be construed as including areference to the`
  line `commuted value of the pension.`
