obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line 73
  line `THE ELEVENTH SCHEDULE`
  line `[ See section 85(7)(e)]`
  line `Principles governing the functioning of the River Management Boards.`
  line `1. The operation protocol notified by the Ministry of Water Resources with respect to water resources`
  line `arrived at b ased on appropriate dependability criteria after the adjudication by the Krishna Water Disputes`
  line `Tribunal shall be binding on both the successor States.`
  line `2. In the event of conflicting demand of water for irrigation and power, the requirement of water for`
  line `irrigation shall take precedence.`
  line `3. In the event of conflicting demand of water for irrigation and drinking water, therequirement of`
  line `water for drinking water purpose shall take precedence.`
  line `4. The allocations made by the River Water Tribunals with regard to various projectson Godavari and`
  line `Krishna Rivers or for the regions of the existing State of Andhra Pradesh, in respect of assured water shall`
  line `remain the same.`
  line `5. Allocations, if any, to be made on excess flows by any Tribunal in future shall be binding on both`
  line `the State of Telangana and the successor State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `6. While the successor State Governments shall be responsible for managing naturalcalamities, the`
  line `Boards shall advise the two State Governments on the management of disaster or drought or flood in the`
  line `rivers of Krishna and Godavari, particularly in reference to the release of water for the management and`
  line `mitigation of the natural calamities. The Boards shall have the full authority to get their orders`
  line `implemented by the two successor State Governments promptly and effectively in respect of operation of`
  line `the head works of the dams, reservoirs or head works of canals and works appurtenant thereto including`
  line `the hydel power projects, as notified by the Central Government, on Krishna and Godavari Rivers.`
  line `7. No new projects based on water resources arrived at based on appropriate dependability criteria on`
  line `Godavari or Krishna rivers can be taken up by the State of Telanganaor the State of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `without obtaining sanction from the Apex Council on Riverwater resources. All such proposals shall be`
  line `first appraised and technically cleared by therespective Board, before sanction by the said Apex Council.`
  line `8. Execution of ongoing projects and future new projects on Godavari and Krishna rivers shall be the`
  line `responsibility of the State Government concerned where the project is located.`
  line `9. In case of non - implementation of the decision by either of the States, the defaulting State shall bear`
  line `the responsibility and shall face financial and other penalties imposed by the Central Government.`
  line `10. The following irrigation projects which are under construction shall be completed as per the plan`
  line `notified by the existing State of Andhra Pradesh and the water sharing arrangement shall continue as`
  line `such: —`
  line `(i) Handri Niva`
  line `(ii) Telugu Ganga`
  line `(iii) Galeru Nagiri`
  line `(iv) Venegondu`
  line `(v) Kalvakurthi`
  line `(vi) Nettempadu.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
