  sourcePage 74
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line 74
  line `THE TWELFTH SCHEDULE`
  line `( See section 92)`
  line `A. Coal`
  line `1. Of the total equity of Singareni Collieries Company Ltd. (SCCL), 51% shall be with the`
  line `Government of Telangana and 49% with the Government of India.`
  line `2. Existing coal linkages of SCCL shall continue without any change.`
  line `3. New linkages shall be allotted to the successor States as per the New Coal Distribution Policy by`
  line `Government of India.`
  line `4. End use plants of the allocated coal blocks shall continue with coal from the blockto be supplied in`
  line `proportion to their respective capacities.`
  line `B. Oil and Gas`
  line `1. Allocation of natural gas will continue to be done as per the policies and guidelines issued by the`
  line `Government of India from time to time.`
  line `2. The royalties payable on domestic onshore production of oil and gas shall accrue to the State in`
  line `which such production takes place.`
  line `C. Power`
  line `1. Units of APGENCO shall be divided based on geographical location of power plants.`
  line `2. Existing Power Purchase Agreements (PPAs) with respective DISCOMS shall continue for both`
  line `on - going projects and projects under construction.`
  line `3. The existing Andhra Pradesh Electricity Regulatory Commission (APERC) shall function as a joint`
  line `regulatory body for a period not exceeding six months within which time separate SERCs will be formed`
  line `in the successor States.`
  line `4. The existing State Load Despatch Centre (SLDC) shall function for both successor States for a`
  line `period not exceeding two years within which time separate SLDC shall be set up for each successor State.`
  line `During this period, the existing SLDC shall function under the direct administration and control of the`
  line `Southern RLDC at Bengaluru.`
  line `5. Transmission lines of APTRANSCO of 132 KV and higher voltage cutting across the successor`
  line `States shall be deemed as Inter - State Transmission System (ISTS) lines. The transmission lines falling`
  line `within the territory of each successor State shall be transferred to the respective State Transmission`
  line `Utilities. The maintenance of ISTS lines shall also be done by successor States in their respective`
  line jurisdictions.
  line `6. The power of the Central Generating Stations will be allotted in such ratio to the State of Telangana`
  line `and the State of Andhra Pradesh based on the actual energy consumption of the last 5 years of the relevant`
  line `DISCOMS in the respective successor State.`
  line `7. For a period of ten years, the successor State that has a deficit of electricity shall have the first right`
  line `of refusal for the purchase of surplus power from the other successor State.`
  line `8. The districts of Anantapur and Kurnool which fall within the jurisdiction of the AP Central Power`
  line `Distribution Company Ltd. will now be reassigned to the AP South Power Distribution Company Ltd.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
