obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line 75
  line `THE THIRTEENTH SCHEDULE`
  line `( See section 93)`
  line Education
  line `1. The Government of India shall take steps to establish institutions of national importance in the 12th`
  line `and 13th Plan periods in the successor State of AndhraPradesh. This would include one IIT, one NIT, one`
  line `IIM, one IISER, one Central University, one Petroleum University, one Agricultural University and one`
  line IIIT.
  line `2. The Government of India shall establish one AIIMS - type Super - Specialty Hospitalcum - Teaching`
  line `Institution in the successor State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `3. The Government of India shall establish a Tribal University each in the State of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `and in the State of Telangana.`
  line `4. A Horticulture University shall be established in the successor State of Telangana.`
  line `5. The Government of India shall establish the National Institute of Disaster Management in the`
  line `successor State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line Infrastructure
  line `1. The Government of India shall develop a new major port at Duggirajupatnam in the successor State`
  line `of Andhra Pradesh to be completed in phases with Phase I by end - 2018;`
  line `2. SAIL shall examine, within six months from the appointed day, the feasibility of establishing an`
  line `integrated steel plant in Khammam district of the successor State of Telangana;`
  line `3. SAIL shall, within six months from the appointed day, examine the feasibility of establishing an`
  line `integrated Steel Plant in YSR District of the successor State of Andhra Pradesh;`
  line `4. IOC or HPCL shall, within six months from the appointed day, examine the feasibility of`
  line `establishing a greenfield crude oil refinery and petrochemical complex in the successor State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh and take an expeditious decision thereon;`
  line `5. The Government of India shall, within six months from the appointed day, examine the feasibility`
  line `of establishing a Vizag - Chennai industrial corridor along the lines of Delhi - Mumbai Industrial Corridor`
  line `and take within such period an expeditious decision thereon;`
  line `6. The Government of India shall, within six months from the appointed day, examine the feasibility`
  line `of expanding the existing Visakhapatnam, Vijayawada and Tirupatiairports to international standards and`
  line `take an expeditious decision thereon;`
  line `7. NTPC shall establish a 4000 MW power facility in the successor State of Telangana after`
  line `establishing necessary coal linkages;`
  line `8. Indian Railways shall, within six months from the appointed day, examine establishinga new`
  line `railway zone in the successor State of Andhra Pradesh and take an expeditious decision thereon;`
  line `9. NHAI shall take necessary steps to improve road connectivity in the backward regions of the`
  line `successor State of Telangana;`
  line `10. The Indian Railways shall, within six months from the appointed day, examine the feasibility of`
  line `establishing a Rail Coach Factory in the successor State of Telangana and improve rail connectivity in the`
  line `State and take an expeditious decision thereon;`
  line `11. The Central Government shall take measures to establish rapid rail and road connectivity from the`
  line `new capital of the successor State of Andhra Pradesh to Hyderabad and other important cities of`
  line Telangana;
  line `12. The Government of India shall examine the feasibility of Metro Rail facility in Vishakhapatnam`
  line `and Vijayawada - Guntur - Tenali Metropolitan Urban Development Authority within a period of one year`
  line `from the appointed day and take an expeditious decision thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-76
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Page 76`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  sourcePage 76
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line 76
  line `STATEMENT OF OBJECTS AND REASONS`
  line `The creation of a separate State of Telangana for the betterment of the social, economic, political and`
  line `other aspirations of the people of that region has been a long standing demand. Pursuant thereto, the`
  line `Government of India on 9th December, 2009 announced that the process for formation of a separate State`
  line `of Telangana would be initiated. After wide - ranging consultations on 3rd October, 2013, the Government`
  line `of India decided to bifurcate the existing State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line `2. The Andhra Pradesh Reorganisation Bill, 2014 seeks to give effect to the aforesaid decision. It aims`
  line `at reconstituting the existing State of Andhra Pradesh into two separate States, namely the State of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh and the State of Telangana. The proposed reorganisation will meet the democratic aspirations of`
  line `the people of Telangana region and ensure peace, goodwill, progress and prosperity among all the`
  line `sections of the people of both successor States.`
  line `3. The salient features of the said Bill, inter alia, are as follows: —`
  line `( a ) it provides for the territories of the two successor States of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana,`
  line `and necessary provisions relating to representation in Parliament and State Legislatures, distribution`
  line `of revenues, apportionment of assets and liabilities, mechanisms for the management and`
  line `development of water resources, power and natural resources and other matters;`
  line `( b ) it makes provisions for the maintenance of law and order to ensure peace and harmony in all`
  line `regions and districts of the two successor States after the appointed day;`
  line `( c ) it provides that Hyderabad in the existing State of Andhra Pradesh shall be the common`
  line `capital of both the successor States from the appointed day for a period not exceeding ten years, and`
  line `puts in place legal and administrative measures to ensure that both the State Governments can`
  line `function efficiently from the common capital which includes the area notified as Greater Hyderabad`
  line `Municipal Corporation under the Hyderabad Municipal Corporation Act, 1955;`
  line `( d ) it makes provisions casting responsibility on the Central Government to assist the successor`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh in identification of its new capital and to assist that State financially in the`
  line `creation of essential facilities in the new capital;`
  line `( e ) it further makes provisions casting responsibility on the Central Government to promote`
  line `industrialisation and economic growth in both the successor States through fiscal measures as well as`
  line `through other programmes for the development of backward areas, in particular Rayalaseema and the`
  line `north coastal regions of the successor State of Andhra Pradesh, by special development package to be`
  line `given by the Central Government after having due regard to the resources available to the successor`
  line `State of Andhra Pra desh;`
  line `( f ) it declares that the Polavaram irrigation project will be a national project which would be`
  line `executed by the Central Government expeditiously;`
  line `( g ) it enables the Central Government to expeditiously provide for the industrialisation as well as`
  line `infrastructure development relating to education, power, port, airports, road transport and railways`
  line `for the progress and sustainable development of both the successor States.`
  line `4. The Bill seeks to achieve the aforesaid objectives.`
  line `SUSHILKUMAR SHINDE.`
  line `N EW D ELHI;`
  line `The 8 th February, 2014.`
